sentences: William Michael Morgan (born May 13, 1993) is an American country music singer from Vicksburg, Mississippi.
His debut single "I Met a Girl", reached number two on the Country Airplay chart and number eight on the Hot Country Songs chart in October 2016; the song was co-written with Sam Hunt.
The album's second single "Missing", was released to country radio on November 7, 2016.
His debut studio album Vinyl, was released on September 30, 2016.
Morgan parted ways with Warner Bros. Nashville in January 2019.
William Michael Morgan released 4 Singles in 2018, as the 5 instalments in Morgan's From the Neon Lounge video series.
The first Single From The Neon Lounge is called "Tonight Girl".

He has performed more than 50 times on the Grand Ole Opry and was featured by the Country Music Hall of Fame and Museum as a highlighted artist in the 2017 American Currents exhibit.
